Food Menu Application with Node.js and MongoDB

This is a Node.js application for managing a food menu with "admin" and "user" roles. The application uses MongoDB for data storage.

Features
Admin: Login, menu management (categories and food items), user management.
User: Signup, login, profile editing, view menu.

Extra Functionalities

TypeScript: Implementation using TypeScript for better code quality.
AWS S3 Integration: Menu image upload to AWS S3 for efficient storage.

Prerequisites

Node.js
MongoDB
typeScript
AWS S3 Account (for menu image upload)

Getting Started

Clone the repository and install dependencies.

Configure MongoDB and AWS S3 credentials.

Run the application and access it at http://localhost:3000.

